message:
Excellent article plus all your answers on stack overflow relating to async are always just what I'm looking for. Quick question, altering your example to show what I mean, is there a reason you should / should not do the following?

public Task DoOperationsConcurrentlyAsync()  
{  
 Task[] tasks = new Task[3];  
 tasks[0] = DoOperation0Async();  
 tasks[1] = DoOperation1Async();  
 tasks[2] = DoOperation2Async();

 // At this point, all three tasks are running at the same time.

 return Task.WhenAll(tasks);  
}

public async Task SomeOtherOperation()  
{  
 //some stuff  
 await DoOperationsConcurrentlyAsync();  
 //more stuff  
}

So I guess my question is should I always be using async and awaiting in the method and is there drawbacks of doing so or not doing so?
